Everted hemipenes of BNHS 3537 (
Fig. 6
) short (ca. 
2.5 mm
), stout (ca. 1.0 mm wide at base). Interpreted as unilobed but with substantial medial lobe-like process (lacking any sign of sulcus spermaticus) ca. 1.0 mm from tip of organ. Medial process shorter and more slender than lobe, with irregular longitudinal folds. Lobe subcylindrical, ornamented densely with small spines throughout; shallow sulcus spermaticus terminating at base of lobe with large flap and several globular folds.
